<chapter xml:id="ch-empty" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>numbering bug?</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>the following is an <c>&lt;ol&gt;</c> but numbers don't appear</p>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <me>a^2+b^2=c^2</me>
      </li>
      <li>
        <me>a^2+b^2=c^2</me>
      </li>
    </ol>
      <ol>
                <li><me>\begin{matrix}
 x &amp;  +  &amp; 2 \, y &amp;  +  &amp; z &amp; = &amp; 2 \\
 3 \, x &amp;  +  &amp; 4 \, y &amp;  &amp;  &amp; = &amp; 9 \\
 &amp;  -  &amp; y &amp;  -  &amp; 2 \, z &amp; = &amp; 3 \\
 -3 \, x &amp;  -  &amp; 4 \, y &amp;  -  &amp; z &amp; = &amp; -6 \\
 \end{matrix}</me></li>
                <li><me>\left[\begin{array}{ccc|c}
1 &amp; 2 &amp; 1 &amp; 2 \\
3 &amp; 4 &amp; 0 &amp; 9 \\
0 &amp; -1 &amp; -2 &amp; 3 \\
-3 &amp; -4 &amp; -1 &amp; -6
\end{array}\right]</me></li>
      </ol>
</introduction>

<example checkit-seed="4419" checkit-slug="LE1" checkit-title="Linear systems, vector equations, and augmented matrices">
  <statement>
        <p>Consider the vector equation.</p>
              <me>x_{1} \left[\begin{array}{c}
1 \\
3 \\
0 \\
-3
\end{array}\right] + x_{2} \left[\begin{array}{c}
2 \\
4 \\
-1 \\
-4
\end{array}\right] + x_{3} \left[\begin{array}{c}
1 \\
0 \\
-2 \\
-1
\end{array}\right] = \left[\begin{array}{c}
2 \\
9 \\
3 \\
-6
\end{array}\right]</me>
        <ol>
            <li> Write a system of scalar equations corresponding to this vector equation. </li>
            <li> Write an augmented matrix corresponding to this vector equation. </li>
        </ol>
  </statement>

  <solution>
     <ol>
                <li><me>\begin{matrix}
 x &amp;  +  &amp; 2 \, y &amp;  +  &amp; z &amp; = &amp; 2 \\
 3 \, x &amp;  +  &amp; 4 \, y &amp;  &amp;  &amp; = &amp; 9 \\
 &amp;  -  &amp; y &amp;  -  &amp; 2 \, z &amp; = &amp; 3 \\
 -3 \, x &amp;  -  &amp; 4 \, y &amp;  -  &amp; z &amp; = &amp; -6 \\
 \end{matrix}</me></li>
                <li><me>\left[\begin{array}{ccc|c}
1 &amp; 2 &amp; 1 &amp; 2 \\
3 &amp; 4 &amp; 0 &amp; 9 \\
0 &amp; -1 &amp; -2 &amp; 3 \\
-3 &amp; -4 &amp; -1 &amp; -6
\end{array}\right]</me></li>
      </ol>
    </solution>
</example>
